title: Seminar and exhibition on achievements of Healthy Ageing Campaign
content_text: The Elderly Commission today (June 5) held a seminar and a two-day exhibition on the achievements of the Healthy Ageing Campaign. Funded by the Hong Kong Jockey Club Charities Trust, the three-year campaign was launched in 2001 and aimed to promote a proper concept on ageing in the community to improve the physical and psychosocial well being of current and future generations of the older population. In the past three years, the Commission had organised public education and publicity programmes as well as funded community partnership programmes of various organisations to widely disseminate healthy ageing
